notesStmt.note: In Anglo-Norman, with one exception; many are translations from Latin.
Very few annotations and one manicule (leaf 196v).
Notes in various later hands on leaf 1.
Ricci, S. de. Census of medieval and Renaissance manuscripts in the United States and Canada, 1073.1.

msContents.summary: A collection of statutes of the realm [manuscript], compiled ca. 1325. Abbreviated versions. Includes an Anglo-Norman version of the 1225 reissue of Magna Carta.

msItem.title: A collection of statutes of the realm manuscript, compiled ca. 1325.

respStmt.persName: Folger, Emily C. J. (Emily Clara Jordan), 1858-1936, former owner.

msItem.title: [Statute of Bigamy, followed by other shorter statutes]

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 18-21 long lines (dimensions of written space: 90 x 58 mm); below line; frame-ruled; prickings in outer margin; headings on top of each page; pen flourishes of letters on last line of page.

decoDesc.decoNote: Simple blue, red and gold borders on leaves 2r-12v; Gold initials with red and blue ink flourishes on leaves 14r, 31v, 54r, 59r, 86v, 144r, 152r, 161v, 166v, 185r, and 186v; Pen flourished initials in red and blue ink throughout; Red and blue initials and highlights throughout.

binding.p: Bound in original limp vellum covers; spine has been removed and quires resewn.

origin.p: Written in English in beginning of 14th century; ca. 1325

history.provenance: Note on leaf 1v: Gift of John Gomme of Charley [?], December 3, 1821; Acquired by Henry Clay Folger from E. Williams of Hove, May 1922.
